:: That time in high school.. {"position":"600,925","size":"100,100"}
<audio controls autoplay loop>
  <source src="boxmonologue.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">
</audio>

(click: ?page)[==
I took this, um, vo-tech class in high school, 
woodworking. Well, I took a lot of vo-tech classes 'cause it was just a big jerk-off. But 
this one time, I had this teacher, name of, um, 
Mr., uh, Mr. Pike. 
Guess he was, like, a Marine or something before he got old. He was hard of hearing. My, uh, my project for his class was to make this, 
um, wooden box, you know, like a small, um... 
Just like a, like a box, you know, to put stuff in. 
So I, I wanted to get the thing done as fast as possible. Um, I figured I could cut classes for the rest of the semester and he couldn't flunk me as long as I, you know, made the thing. 
So I finished it in a couple days, and it looked... It was pretty lame, but it worked, you know, for putting stuff in or whatnot. 
So when I, uh, showed it to Mr. Pike 
for my grade, 
uh, he looked at it and said, 
"Is that the best you can do?" 
At first I thought to myself, "Hell yeah, bitch. Now give me a D and shut up so I can go blaze one with my boys." 
I don't know. Maybe it was the way he said it, but 
it was like he, he wasn't exactly saying it sucked. He was just asking me honestly, "Is, 
is that all you got?" 
And for some reason, I thought to myself, 
"Yeah, man, I, I can do better." So I started from scratch. I made another, then another, and by the end of the semester, by, like, box number five, 
I had built this thing. 
You should have seen it. It was insane. 
I mean, I built it out of Peruvian walnut with inlaid zebrawood. 
It was fitted with pegs, no screws. I sanded it for days until 
it was smooth as glass. Then I rubbed all the wood with tung oil so it was rich and dark. 
It even smelled good. You know, you put your nose in it and breathed in. 
It was... It was perfect. 
I, um, 
I gave it to my mom. 
You know, I didn't give the box to my mom. 
I traded it for an ounce of weed.
[[Anyway...]]


:: hahahahaha {"position":"700,1375","size":"100,100"}
“Hey, whatever, man.”

“YOU just need to keep those junkies in line. They still believe that you killed that other junkie.”

“Yeah, man. Alright, man.” 

It always ends up like this with Mr. White. He’s so anal. 
(click: ?page)[==
Ring ring ring. 
(click: ?page)[==
“Yo wassup Pete. Yo, chill out…”
(click: ?page)[==
The way Pete is talking, you can barely understand. What is he talking about?
(click: ?page)[==
“Is that Skinny Pete? Let me see that.”
(click: ?page)[==
The phone slips out of your hands. What the hell was Pete talking about? 
(click: ?page)[==
“Pete? What’s that? Combo? Who the hell is Combo? No, Jesse is… he’s doing something.” 
(click: ?page)[==
“Did he have product on him? You quit? What do you mean, you quit. Hey, come to Jesse’s flat and we’ll talk, alright? 
(click: ?page)[==
No, I don’t know who killed Combo! Just COME and we can talk about things, okay?” 
(click: ?page)[==
There’s a lump in your throat but you don’t know why.

(click: ?page)[==
Swallow the spit. 
(click: ?page)[==
It won’t go down.
(click: ?page)[==
Combo? Didn’t you just see him on your way here? 
(click: ?page)[==
“Pete? Peter? Dammit! Jesse, help me out here.”
(click: ?page)[==
That’s weird… and he was holding a cake. 
(click: ?page)[==
A cake?
(click: ?page)[==
“Jesse.” 
(click: ?page)[==
Why the hell did he have a cake? 
(click: ?page)[==
“Jesse!” 
(click: ?page)[==
Oh, duh… ‘cause tomorrow is Ms. Ortega’s birthday.


:: other passage {"position":"700,400","size":"100,100"}
It’s morning. 
You’re just now blinking awake. 
Jane’s still sleeping next to you.
Whenever you wake up next to her, you notice that she sounds kinda catlike with her little snores. A little snrrrrk, snrrrrk purring gently beside	s you. It’s nice. Jane’s cool.

You are Jesse Pinkman, certified high school burnout, 26 and 5’9 in stocking feet, and co-producer of the finest scante this side of the border. 

All this, and it’s time to get up for the day.

[[Light a joint]] 
[[Not right now]] 
